       <h1>Properties of Error Instances</h1>
-      <p>Error instances are ordinary objects that inherit properties from the Error prototype object and have an [[ErrorData]] internal slot whose value is *undefined*. The only specified use of [[ErrorData]] is to identify Error, AggregateError, and _NativeError_ instances as Error objects within `Object.prototype.toString` and `Error.isError`.</p>
+      <p>Error instances are ordinary objects that inherit properties from the Error prototype object and have an [[ErrorData]] internal slot whose value is *undefined*. Specified uses of [[ErrorData]] include to identify <emu-xref href="#sec-error-constructor">Error</emu-xref>, <emu-xref href="#sec-aggregate-error-constructor">AggregateError</emu-xref>, and _NativeError_ instances as Error objects within <emu-xref href="#sec-object.prototype.tostring">Object.prototype.toString</emu-xref> and <emu-xref href="#sec-error.iserror">Error.isError</emu-xref>; as well as for the <emu-xref href="#sec-error.prototype.stack">Error.prototype.stack accessor</emu-xref>.</p>
     </emu-clause>
 
